+ User Authentication

++ Set up a minimal authentication source

<code type="bash">
$ htpasswd -c -s /home/username/htpasswd.conf username
New password: 
Re-type new password: 
Adding password for user username
</code>

++ Edit Solar.config.php to point to the authentication source

<code type="bash">
$ vi Solar.config.php
</code>

<code type="php">
$config = array();

// SQL connection
$config['Solar_Sql'] = array(
	'adapter' => 'Solar_Sql_Adapter_Mysql',
	'config'  => array(
    	'host'   => '127.0.0.1',
    	'user'   => 'username',
    	'pass'   => 'password',
    	'name'   => 'database',
	),
);

// Front controller HREF prefix
$config['Solar_Uri_Action']['path'] = '/index.php';

// Public directory HREF prefix
$config['Solar_Uri_Public']['path'] = '/public';

// Authentication source
$config['Solar_User']['auth']['adapter'] = 'Solar_Auth_Adapter_Htpasswd';
$config['Solar_User']['auth']['config']['file'] = '/home/username/htpasswd.conf';

// Done!
return $config;
</code>

++ Browse to "Hello World"

``http://example.com/index.php/hello``

Attempt to log in with your username and password.


